OL,3,CFree music lessons for school pupils
OL,4,Ccould be lost in council cuts
OL,6,FPupils who benefitted from free in-
OL,7,Fschool music tuition have reacted with
OL,8,Fdisappointment to proposals to cut the
OL,9,Fservice, as a council battles with
OL,10,Fbalancing the books.
OL,12,FDumfries and Galloway Council faces a
OL,13,Fshortfall of #35million over the next
OL,14,Fthree years, and is now running a
OL,15,Fconsultation to gather views on which
OL,16,Fservices to cut.
OL,18,FScrapping free in-school music tuition
OL,19,Ffor P5-S6 pupils is one proposal,
OL,20,Fwhich the council says would save up
OL,21,Fto #564,000 between 2026 and 2029.
